ogle.com/maps/contrib/112275232644298872770/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Planting &amp; Gardening FAQs</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much does professional tree and shrub planting cost in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Per-plant pricing in Las Cruces typically runs $150 to $250 for a 5-gallon shrub installed (plant, dig, amend, water-in, mulch), $300 to $800 for a 15-gallon tree, and $1,000 to $2,500 for a 24-inch box or larger specimen tree. Full bed installs (mixed shrubs and perennials with drip) run $1,500 to $5,000 depending on size. Multi-tree property planting and large landscape installs run $5,000 to $15,000. Pricing covers soil amendment, hole sizing, root prep, and watering-in. The on-site consultation is always free.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">When is the best time to plant trees and shrubs in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Fall (mid-September through November) is the gold-standard planting window in Las Cruces. Soil is still warm enough for roots to grow, air temps are dropping, and the plant has six months to establish before next summer's heat. Spring (March through April) is the second-best window. We avoid mid-summer planting (June through August) when possible because the heat stress on a freshly-installed root ball is brutal. We can hold a planting schedule and pre-order plants from regional growers so they arrive fresh on install day.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Can you actually plant in caliche soil?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes, but it has to be done right. We dig planting holes at least twice the diameter of the root ball (sometimes three times), break through the caliche layer where we can, and backfill with a mix of native soil amended with compost. For trees, the hole goes deeper than the root ball so we can crack the caliche bottom and create drainage. For shrubs, we test how fast water drains out of the hole before backfilling. If the hole holds water for 24+ hours, we move it or build a slight mound. Most plant deaths in Las Cruces are caused by planting into untreated caliche, not the plant choice.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What plants survive Las Cruces summers and our drought conditions?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Native and desert-adapted species. Trees: desert willow, chitalpa, honey mesquite, Texas mountain laurel, New Mexico locust. Shrubs: Apache plume, Texas sage, three-leaf sumac, fernbush, cliffrose. Perennials: salvia, agastache, gaura, penstemon, blackfoot daisy. Architectural: yucca, agave, sotol, red yucca, ocotillo. Grasses: blue grama (the New Mexico state grass), deer grass, Mexican feather grass. Cool-season turf, hydrangeas, azaleas, and most temperate-climate plants almost always fail here. We can preview most species growing in real Las Cruces conditions at the Las Cruces Utilities demonstration garden.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How long do I need to baby a newly planted tree before it's established?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Plan on supplemental water for the first full year, with most of the attention in the first 90 days. Weeks one through four: deep water two to three times a week, slowly enough that water soaks down 12+ inches. Months two and three: deep water once or twice a week. Months four through twelve: once a week, more in summer, less in winter. Year two: most native and desert-adapted trees can taper to once every two to three weeks. Drip irrigation makes this easy. We program your controller to the exact schedule and hand off a written watering plan.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you guarantee the plants you install?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. We offer industry-leading plant guarantees on every installation, plus a workmanship guarantee on the soil prep, drip, and hole work. The plants we install come from regional growers that supply Las Cruces. If a plant fails within the guarantee period because of how it was installed, we replace it at no charge. Plants that fail because of owner-side issues (controller turned off, dog dug it up, freeze damage outside the guarantee window) we'll diagnose and recommend a fix.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you handle full landscape design or just installation?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Both. For a single tree or a fill-in shrub, we'll just plant. For a bed install, a yard refresh, or a full property planting, we offer in-house landscape design. We'll meet on-site, talk goals and water budget, and produce a planting plan with species, sizes, spacing, and irrigation zones. Larger projects can include 3D renderings before any digging starts. Design and installation under one roof, by the same team.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Will the planting plan comply with the Las Cruces water ordinance?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. We design every planting plan around drip irrigation, group plants by water need so each zone runs only as long as it has to, and program controllers to your address parity (even-numbered addresses water Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday; odd water Wednesday, Friday, Sunday; no Mondays; no daytime watering April 1 through September 30). Newly installed plants get a documented establishment-period exemption from many of the ordinance restrictions. We hand off a written watering plan that walks you through each zone.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-related-184"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Beyond Planting</span><h2 class="cs-title">More Services in Las Cruces</h2><p class="cs-text">Planting pairs naturally with the rest of what we install. Same in-house crews. Same workmanship guarantee.</p></div><ul class="cs-related-list"><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscape-design/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Landscape Design</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Custom planting plans, site layouts, and 3D renderings before any digging starts.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Full water-wise landscape conversions with native plants, drip, and mulch on a single contract.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscaping/raised-garden-beds/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Raised Garden Beds</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Custom-built cedar, stone, and metal beds for vegetables, herbs, and ornamentals above the caliche.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/drip-irrigation/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Drip Irrigation</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Whole-yard drip systems sized to your plant zones and the Las Cruces watering ordinance.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscape-maintenance/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Pruning, weed control, and seasonal color rotations that keep new plantings looking sharp.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Ready to Plant the Yard?</h2><a href="/contact/" class="cs-talk-button">Schedule Free Consultation</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-grass"></section>
